<plot>Up against her own sense of failure with caring for her dying parents, the filmmaker searches for people who might have found success. Marcia and Rick struggle with their new relationship while one of them readies to die; Christine's mother and stepfather are dying, but she can only care for one of them; and in one long night Frank Ostaseski discovers he is more than "Mr. Hospice." Better than a primer for success, the film reveals a recipe for forgiveness.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?094403</url></doc>
